# Copy this file to .env (which is gitignored) before running `docker compose up`.
# Override the defaults for local development.
#
# This lab runs THREE Ignition gateways (local / dev / prod). Each gateway has
# its own admin credentials and its own API key. Local credentials are used
# at first login; dev/prod credentials are only needed when you click into
# those gateways' UIs.
#
# The API key below matches the pre-provisioned `cicd` token committed in
# services/config/resources/core/ignition/api-token/ (the gateway stores only
# the SHA-256 hash of the secret; the full name:secret key is the value here).
# All three gateways carry the same token — local via the bind mount, dev/prod
# because setup.sh seeds it into gateways/<gw>/config before their first boot
# (and every deploy copies it back fresh) — so the SAME key works everywhere.
# Its security levels (APIToken Access/Read/Write) grant the scan endpoints. For CI, IGNITION_API_KEY_DEV / _PROD are duplicated as GitHub
# environment secrets named IGNITION_API_KEY on the lab-gateway-dev /
# lab-gateway-prod environments. See README.md for the full setup.

# ---- Local gateway (http://localhost:8088) ------------------------------
GATEWAY_ADMIN_USERNAME_LOCAL=admin
GATEWAY_ADMIN_PASSWORD_LOCAL=password
IGNITION_API_KEY_LOCAL=cicd:i5elT52UZSKUWYp6nEiek3XJmECOZeH-b2cM2hPa2ts

# ---- Dev gateway (http://localhost:8089) — deploy.yml target ------------
GATEWAY_ADMIN_USERNAME_DEV=admin
GATEWAY_ADMIN_PASSWORD_DEV=password
IGNITION_API_KEY_DEV=cicd:i5elT52UZSKUWYp6nEiek3XJmECOZeH-b2cM2hPa2ts

# ---- Prod gateway (http://localhost:8090) — deploy.yml target=prod ------
GATEWAY_ADMIN_USERNAME_PROD=admin
GATEWAY_ADMIN_PASSWORD_PROD=password
IGNITION_API_KEY_PROD=cicd:i5elT52UZSKUWYp6nEiek3XJmECOZeH-b2cM2hPa2ts

# ---- Backward-compat single key (optional) ------------------------------
# Older scripts/CI workflows that don't set a per-gateway key fall back to
# this. You can leave it unset; scan.sh will pick the right
# IGNITION_API_KEY_<GATEWAY> based on the --gateway flag.
# IGNITION_API_KEY=

# ---- Shared TimescaleDB sidecar ------------------------------------------
# One Postgres instance, three databases (ignition_loc, ignition_dev,
# ignition_prd), and two logins: `ignition` (superuser — the TimescaleDB
# connection) and `reporting` (read-only — the TimescaleDB_Reports
# connection, created by db-init/ on first volume init).
#
# These values are rung 1 of the secrets ladder: env vars that anyone can
# `docker inspect` out of the containers. Part 1A of the lab moves them into
# files under secrets/ — keep the SAME values when you do (they match
# secrets/*.example): Postgres only sets passwords on first volume init, so
# a new value here would not change an existing database.
POSTGRES_USER=ignition
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=lab06-postgres-pw
REPORTING_PASSWORD=lab06-reporting-pw

# ---- GitHub Actions self-hosted runner ----------------------------------
# The bundled runner registers with a short-lived registration token — no PAT.
# scripts/setup.sh mints that token for you with the GitHub CLI (the same no-PAT
# method Lab 03 uses), so all you set here is your fork's URL. Just make sure gh
# is installed and authenticated first: `gh auth login`.
#
# RUNNER_REPO_URL is your fork (not the upstream mustry-academy repo).
RUNNER_REPO_URL=https://github.com/<your-github-user>/cicd-lab-06-multi-gateway-deploy
RUNNER_NAME=lab06-runner
